All long-term care facilities shall retain the following for public inspection in the office of the administrator and in the lobby of the facility:
A complete copy of every inspection report of the facility received from the cabinet during the past three (3) years, including the most recent inspection report;
A description of the services currently provided by the facility;
A listing of the rates currently charged for services provided by the facility;
A listing together with the charges for the services and items not included in the basic rate for which residents may be charged separately; and
A copy of every court order issued pertaining to the quality of care or services provided in the facility.
